VPSK pistols are made in Heckler & Koch's Oberndorf factory in southwest Germany and are well suited for civilian sport shooting, security, military, and law enforcement use. title: For Sale/Trade:  Norinco SKS D, Uses AK Mags Complete w/ 9 Mags, Ammo, Scope, Sling
postcontent:
Norinco SKS Model D with Vomz P8x56 Scope
9 - 30 round AK Magazines
Leather Russian AK Sling
400+ rounds 7.62x39 Ammo
Tapco Synthetic Folding Stock
 
Not a tack driver but it is a kick to shoot without breaking the bank.
It was part of a trade deal and just doesn’t fit into what I shoot.
It is extremely clean front to back. Shiney bore and all surfaces clean. No issues with anything that I saw.. The only “problem” is original latch for rear housing has been replaced with a straight pin as opposed to a “L” shaped latch.
It was in a Tapco synthetic stock and the young man I got it from had decided to paint the original wood stock camo. Needless to say I stripped it down and reoiled it to its original finish. I just like the original look better, but I am including the Tapco stock as well. No Problems with it I just am not fond of them.
I deburred the trigger assembly as well, so runs as smooth as any SKS I have ever shot.
Took it to the range and it shot fine and gets a lot of looks taking AK mags.
I have since changed it back to wood stock and have not sighted it in.
It will never be a “sniper” rifle but it does good and will put them where you want.
Depends on what you read, but the VOMZ P8x56 is nice I feel. A bit big for an SKS but what the hell. I am also including the original rear housing, if buyer decides they don’t want it scoped. Also somewhat unique to this SKS is that the Spike bayonet is removable, it can be unclipped from the bayonet lug without tools.
These are damn near indestructible and will last well beyond a great deal of the stuff made today.
 
I believe that these were imported into the US starting in 1988 (only year they were allowed to be imported with the bayonet). Subsequent imports had the bayonet and lug removed.
The "D" is not really a model, just what dealer's started calling them due to the detachable magazine. You won't see a "D" stamp or anything like that.
A true "D" model will have a 20" barrel, with the bayonet lug and spike bayonet attached. The stock would be in the standard configuration, usually with a unsealed finish.
The “D” is one of the hardest to find SKS’s there are. Built for AK Mags not reworked for fit. Spike bayonet (detachable), 20” barrel and wood stock. Not many nicer than this one.

There are several folks out there that hope you don't and will try to sell a used gun at MSRP prices . Protect yourself by researching on Factory website for MSRP and several different dealer sites to get an idea what it sells for. The dealer price runs $100 - $200 less than MSRP depending on the gun and a used gun will sell for considerably less . Remember GUNBROKER is an AUCTION site that gives you an idea of the range of prices . Knowledge and patience are paramount !!

postcontent: CHECK TO SEE AVAILABILITY OR TO PURCHASE ONLINE> Heckler & Koch P2000SK 9x19mm MFG # W280-01300 UPC Code # REDACTED34  Heckler & Koch P2000SK 9x19mm MFG # W280-01300 UPC Code # REDACTED34    Like the slightly larger P2000 model, the P2000 SK (subcompact) combines elements of the successful HK USP Compact pistol with recent technological innovations from HK engineers — only in a smaller, more concealable design.     The P2000 SK is available with Law Enforcement Modification (also known as Combat Defense Action) trigger system introduced in 2001 on the USP Compact “LEM” (Law Enforcement Modification) model. This unique pre-cocked hammer system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull and short trigger travel from first to last round fired) with a double action hammer system. The LEM/CDA trigger pull has been reduced to 7.3 – 8.5 pounds of pressure (32.5 – 37.8 Newtons), compared to 12 – 15 pounds (53.4 – 66.7 N) found on many conventional double action pistols. Optional adjustment by an HK certified armorer can bring the trigger pull into the 5.5 pound (24.5 N) range.     Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation — one that prevents unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third pull of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the Subcompact.     The enhanced LEM/CDA trigger system combines the reliability of a double-action revolver trigger with the crisp, precise trigger of a single-action pistol. For shooters that prefer a conventional double-action/single-action pistol, a double-action/single-action variant is also available with a decock button mounted on the rear of the frame. A choice of two simple-to-install grip panels make it easy to custom-fit the P2000 Subcompact to any shooter’s hand. And the same ambidextrous magazine release and dual slide release levers found on the P2000 make handling the Subcompact easy for both right- and left-handed shooters.     A set of abbreviated “industry standard” mounting rails on the P2000 SK enable lights, laser aimers, and other accessories to be added by sliding them onto the open rail system. The HK P2000 SK also can use widely available, reliable USP Compact magazines. title: For Sale:  Springfield XDM 9mm 4.5 Custom Set No Trades
postcontent:
I’m selling my like new XDM 9mm 4.5 handgun. A lot of things have been added to this gun when it was purchased new, originally intended to use it as a concealed/competition gun. The gun has been a complete safe queen and has had less than 400 rounds run through it, during its entire lifetime. Starting off the list I replaced the guide rod with a custom tungsten guide rod. This helps add weight to the front of the gun making it better balanced for faster follow up shots. Next I have a replacement guide rod spring. This heavy wolf spring is great for a trip to the range, or you could use the standard one from the factory which is also included. I replaced the sights with TFO night sites when it was purchased, these sights last fifteen years, so they have thirteen years left of life in them. I added talon grip tape to the grip to aid it for concealed carry. I also replaced the rolling pin to aid the durability and reliability. Unlike the standard rolling pin, the new one will last a lifetime of dry firing. I replaced the striker with a Springer striker to make the weapon more reliable. The striker status indicator has also been replaced with a Powder River Precision titanium indicator to help speed up follow up shots. The xdm includes its original case and accessories. It includes a mag carrier, mag loader, and holster from the factory that now no longer comes with the standard XDM. I also am including a custom made appendix inside the wasteband holster made by concealment solutions for the gun. This is a great holster made with custom kydex, and horseleather. The gun comes with its original 3 magazines.
Let’s break it down
The gun new is valued at $630 new Tungston guide rod $70 Wolf Spring $15 Sights $80 (Not charging for the custom installation $50) Talon Grips $16 Holster $70 Rolling pin $5 Striker $50 Striker status indicator $25
The XDM Mag carrier and holster, aren’t standard anymore, springfield charges $100 for them now.
Cash only, no trades of any kind, not even partial trades. This set is worth appx 1061. I’m asking for $820 I feel this is a fair number. I also have a Gunvault MV500-STD gunsafe.
